Daniel A. LEVY v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 6254. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 15, 1930.

Before DIETRICH and WILBUR, Circuit Judges, and WEBSTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of appellee to docket and dismiss appeal for-failure of appellant to file record and docket cause, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
